# Using Multiple Threads

```java
class A extends Thread
{
    public void run()
    {
        for(int i = 1; i <= 5; i++)
        {
            System.out.println("A : " + i);
        }
    }
}

class B extends Thread
{
    public void run()
    {
        for(int i = 1; i <= 5; i++)
        {
            System.out.println("B : " + i);
        }
    }
}

public class Main
{
    public static void main(String[] args)
    {
        A t1 = new A();
        B t2 = new B();

        t1.start();
        t2.start();
    }
}
```

### Possible Output

```text
A : 1
B : 1
A : 2
B : 2
A : 3
B : 3
...
```

(The order may vary because threads execute independently.)

